
    THE weekend saw a number of road accidents in Gauteng, many leading to fatalities and serious injuries.On Saturday, three people were killed, including a two-year-old boy, and six others were injured after a head-on collision on the R558 near Sebokeng, south of Joburg.ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said paramedics arrived on the scene to find two mangled vehicles.“Paramedics discovered the bodies of a woman and two-year-old boy trapped in the one car while the body of a man was found trapped in the second vehicle. Unfortunately, all three had already succumbed to their multiple injuries.”He said five other people, including a 12-year-old child, were found on the scene.Paramedics treated the patients and provided advanced life support interventions while the critically injured child was airlifted by ER24 helicopter to hospital for urgent treatment.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsu9D0LDfAlSHxeJ5I6tktoqvL2uFNT9XLDuA41dcLC__mF9F_Hk-sg3oquXox3BXqw_9BNy7_uBu2rkYHTDqYQP6nSyr05SSCTSFriNWrf63L0QRte4e93MCeMU8zEk6yHZoGWFH2qOWDQkmyp-C5EqnPI6vLO79azukyOKfOYO7r3zaUjUoSxVp8YbD6w2d9cNtdTxaFnimLclN63dEoq2u9i50W4fYyLLM34R1nPmqIZQMXTVWjAJetcJgPWsnw1SPCildstFVGs92_Cy4440hTYFLGU\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzLbIhSKqyIVSEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
